Re-read the problem statement carefully. The task is to:
1. Read one integer N (the height)
2. Use a for loop from 1 to N
3. In each iteration, print a row of asterisks (number of asterisks = current row number)
4. Move to the next line after each row

Example:
```java
Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
System.out.print("Enter height: ");
int n = input.nextInt();

for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
        System.out.print("*");
    }
    System.out.println();
}
```

